-- U.S. Treasury Names Weideman Chief of Staff Under Lew
-- B y   I a n   K a t z
-- 2013-04-29T22:50:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-29/u-s-treasury-names-weideman-chief-of-staff-under-lew.html
Christian Weideman, the U.S.
Treasury Department’s deputy general counsel, has been named
chief of staff to Secretary Jacob J. Lew, a department official
said today.  Weideman will replace  Mark Patterson , who was chief of
staff under former Treasury Secretary  Timothy F. Geithner  and
has remained on during Lew’s transition. Patterson will remain
at the Treasury until late May.  Weideman is a former associate counsel to President Barack Obama and has worked at law firm Williams & Connolly LLP.  Lew took office as secretary on Feb. 28.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian Katz in Washington at 
 ikatz2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
